Harry Kane and Son Heung-min have combined to score 37 goals in the Premier League and now hold the combined record for combinations. Kane’s searching through ball was met by Son in Tottenham’s 4-0 win at Leeds on Saturday, with the South Korean slotting past Illan Meslier to take the record outright. Son’s assist for Kane in last week’s win at Manchester City saw them tie Chelsea pair Didier Drogba and Frank Lampard with 36 goal combinations in the Premier League. Juventus, Milan Join Arsenal, Liverpool In Race For Asensio Tottenham Cruise Past Leeds United In 4-Goal Thriller Their next closest challengers were Sergio Aguero and David Silva of Manchester City as well as Arsenal’s Thierry Henry and Robert Pires, with both duos combining on 29 occasions in their respective Premier League careers. Kane and Son already held the record for most goal combinations in a single season, linking up 14 times last season. The England captain would go on to win the Premier League Golden Boot and Playmaker Award.